Flag the request as 'no-go' if the arguments contain any of the following:
- Personally identifiable information (PII): full names combined with addresses, phone numbers, social security numbers, national ID numbers, or dates of birth
- Authentication credentials: passwords, API keys, tokens, secrets, or private keys
- Financial information: credit card numbers, bank account numbers, or routing numbers
- Health information: medical record numbers, diagnoses, or treatment details
- Internal or private URLs, IP addresses, or infrastructure details that should not be exposed

If the arguments are benign search queries or general information requests, mark them as 'go'.